  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) in the United States\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations in many countries\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer due diligence\n- Mandatory reporting of large cash transactions\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk sectors\n- International information sharing\n\n4. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- License revocation for financial institutions\n\n5. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial Intelligence Units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial regulators\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
